===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

{{Han simp|𤐫|f=火|t=示|f2=𢍱|t2=覀}}. {{Han compound|火|𢍱|ls=ic|c1=s|c2=s|t1=fire|t2=to rise high}}, which represents two pairs of hands holding and rising an object, perhaps a bag or basket ([[西]]). The character originally represented the idea of sparks rising up. By extension, it was also used to mean "token" or "label."<ref>Digital Shinjigen 2017</ref> Then, the two pair of hands disappeared in the modern version.

Unrelated to the original version of [[要]] and [[栗]].

